msgid "Non-custodial node setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:47
msgid ""
"How to **relinquish control of a node's main account to an external "
"account**, so that the external account's private key is never required "
"in the node setup process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:49
msgid ""
"This is useful, for example, for node providers that work in a **non-"
"custodial** manner. This is, **customers** hire the **node provider** to "
"setup nodes for them and have any node rewards sent to their main "
"accounts, without ever sending their account keys to the node provider."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:51
msgid ""
"There are **many mechanisms** to achieve this in |codename|. This section"
" explains the **simplest one**, assuming that the customer is not tech-"
"savvy and therefore prefers not to use command-line tools like ``symbol-"
"cli``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:53
msgid ""
"**In summary**, once the node is completely setup, full control of the "
"node's **main account** will be transferred to the customer account "
"(called **external account**) by turning main into a :doc:`../../concepts"
"/multisig-account`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:55
msgid ""
"The node provider will prepare a transaction for offline signing and send"
" it to the customer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:56
msgid ""
"The customer signs the transaction using their Wallet from an offline "
"machine, and returns the signature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/guides/network/non-custodial-node-setup.rst:57
msgid "The node provider announces the transaction."
msgstr ""

